The issue with your code is that you are using `PrintWriter.println()` method to write to the file, which adds a newline character at the end of each line. This causes the output to be written to a new line in the file, rather than appending to the existing file. To fix this, you should use `PrintWriter.append()` method instead, which appends the data to the end of the file without adding a newline character.

Here's the modified code that should work as expected:
```java
for(int i = 0; i < A.size(); i++) {
    PrintWriter output = new PrintWriter(csvFile, true); // true means append to the file
    System.out.println(A.get(i) + ", " + B.get(i));
    output.println(A.get(i) + ", " + B.get(i));
}
```
With this modification, the output should be appended to the existing file without overwriting the original data.
